MARKET INFORMATION

For further information please see Rules & Regs.

Who will win this match? At the start of scheduled play all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed therefore it is the responsibility of all customers to manage their own positions. If scores (including a derived target score using the Duckworth Lewis method) are deemed tied at the completion of both innings then all bets on the Match Odds market will be void. Please note there is a separate Tied Match market available for this game. For the avoidance of doubt, if scores are tied at the completion of both innings then any tie breaker that may be used to determine a winner including, but not limited to, bowl outs, Super Overs, one-over eliminators, losing fewer wickets, run rates, coin toss, higher group position does not count for the purposes of this market.

Customers should be aware that:

  • Transmissions described as “live” by some broadcasters may actually be delayed and that all in-play matches are not necessarily televised.

  • The extent of any such delay may vary between customers, depending on the set-up through which they are receiving pictures or data.

Market Information
For further information please see Rules & Regs.

Will there be a result declared in this limited overs match or will it be Abandoned or a No Result? If there is an official result other than No Result the answer will be Yes. Match Abandoned or No Result will mean No. At the start of scheduled play all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed therefore it is the responsibility of all users to manage their own positions.

Customers should be aware that:

  • Transmissions described as “live” by some broadcasters may actually be delayed

  • The extent of any such delay may vary, depending on the set-up through which they are receiving pictures or data.

    • Official Result = Yes

    • Abandoned or No Result = No

    • Please be aware that this bet will carry over onto any reserve day and will be settled on the official result of the match. If a match is postponed or abandoned for any reason other than weather (which may include but is not limited to: dangerous or unplayable wicket or outfield; pitch vandalism; strike or boycott; crowd protests/violence; stadium damage; acts of terrorism; and acts of God), Betfair reserves the right to void all bets on this market.

Will this match end with scores tied? At the scheduled start all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market turned IN PLAY. This market will not be actively managed therefore it is the responsibility of all customers to manage their own positions. For the avoidance of doubt, if scores are tied at the completion of both innings then any tie breaker that may be used to determine a winner including, but not limited to, bowl outs, Super Overs, one-over eliminators, losing fewer wickets, run rates, coin toss, higher group position does not count for the purposes of this market.

Customers should be aware that:

  • Transmissions described as “live” by some broadcasters may actually be delayed and that all in-play matches are not necessarily televised.

  • The extent of any such delay may vary between customers, depending on the set-up through which they are receiving pictures or data.

How many runs will be scored in the FIRST OVER of the stated teams innings? This market will be void if one over is not completed in the stated teams innings unless the result was unconditionally determined. At the start of scheduled play all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed therefore it is the responsibility of all users to manage their own positions. Competition Rules apply.Customers should be aware that:

Which team will score the most sixes in this match? At the start of scheduled play all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed therefore it is the responsibility of all customers to manage their own positions. This market will be settled if 5 overs have been completed in both innings, or if either team is bowled out or has reached its target within 5 overs, or if the market is unconditionally determined. For the avoidance of doubt, if a match finishes in a Tie, then any Bowl Outs, Super Overs or similar which may take place do not count for the purposes of this market. Competition Rules apply.


For the purposes of this market a 'six' is runs scored off the bat that crosses the boundary line without bouncing.

Who will be the Top Batsman for the quoted team in their respective innings? At the start of scheduled play all unmatched bets will be cancelled and this market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed therefore, it is the responsibility of all customers to manage their own positions. This market will be settled if at least one run has been scored from the bat by the named team. Runs scored in Super Overs do not count for the purpose of this market. In the case of a named player being confirmed as a non-runner, bets on that runner will be void. Any runner that is selected in the original starting XI but does not bat will be settled as a loser. Dead heat rules apply.

How many runs will be scored in the listed innings? At the scheduled start time unmatched bets will be cancelled by Betfair and the market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed and it is the responsibility of customers to manage their positions. Bets will stand even if the innings is shortened to less than 20 overs. This market will be settled if 5 overs have been completed in the innings, the batting team is bowled out or has reached the target to win the match. New lines will be added as the team approaches the total. Competition Rules apply.

Customers should be aware that:

  • Transmissions described as “live” by some broadcasters may actually be delayed

  • The extent of any such delay may vary between customers, depending on the set-up through which they are receiving pictures or data.

Market Information
For further information please see Rules & Regs.

How many runs will be scored in the first 10 overs of the listed innings? At the scheduled start time unmatched bets will be cancelled by Betfair and the market will be turned in-play. This market will not be actively managed and it is the responsibility of customers to manage their positions. This market will be settled if 10 overs have been completed in the innings or if the batting side has been bowled out within this period.

For clarification in the event that the batting team does not complete their 10 overs which includes the batting side reaching their target within 10 overs, all bets will be void except if the batting team have been bowled out. Competition Rules apply.

Customers should be aware that:

  • Transmissions described as “live” by some broadcasters may actually be delayed

  • The extent of any such delay may vary between customers, depending on the set-up through which they are receiving pictures or data.
